Eraser : It earses a portion of the picture by using specified eraser size.

Gradient: It fills a color with selected shades of colors.

Paint Bucket: It fills a specific color into the selected
	      area.

Type Tools:
 a) Horizontal Type
 b) Vertical Type
 c) Horizontal Mask
 d) Vertical Mask
 You can use the type tools for inserting text
 into the picture.
    Ctrl + Shift + >     increase font size
    Ctrl + Shift + <     decrease the font size
 Mask allows to select any picture as background for text , instead of color.

Text Options:
 - Font
 - Font Size
 - Style [Bold / Italic]
 - Color
 - Wrap Text [ Arc, Flag, FishEye]

Blending Options 
- Insert text into picture
- Goto Layers panel
- Right Click on Text Layer
- Select "Blending Options"
- Select any blending option like
	a) DropShadow
	b) Outer Glow
	c) Emboss
	d) Color Overlay
	e) Gradient Overlay
	f) Stroke
	g) Pattern Overlay

Grouping Multiple Layers:
- First Right Click on first layer and select
- Press hold down the shift key 
- Right click on second layer and select
- Release the shift key
